<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!-- InfoTriage feeds — verified 2026-06-24.
     ✅ live (HTTP 200 + XML parsed by FreshRSS).
     🟡 transient (HTTP 429 Too Many Requests) — back off and retry safely;
       adjust FreshRSS refresh rate down (≥15 min) so the feed is not
       auto-removed after consecutive failures. Do NOT drop or recreate:
       the upstream is alive, just throttling us (e.g. gdeltproject.org).
     ⚠️ broken or bot-blocked — any of these qualifies:
       - 403 to non-browser UA (Cloudflare / bot block, e.g. ISW);
       - 404 (feed URL retired, e.g. RUSI);
       - 200 OK but body is HTML, not RSS/Atom (XML parser fails —
         e.g. Ukrainska Pravda and The National Interest).
     Flag breakdown (date-stamped to make staleness visible at a glance):
       Currently badged: 12 ⚠️ + 1 🟡. See per-outline lines below for
       which feeds carry each marker.
       History: 5 ⚠️ flagged 2026-06-23 → 8 more ⚠️ flagged 2026-06-24
                → gdeltproject.org migrated → 🟡 2026-06-24.
       Each feed's text="..." attribute carries the live inline marker.
     FreshRSS can't ingest ⚠️ feeds — recreate via rss-bridge
     (http://localhost:3000) or drop. 🟡 feeds must stay listed: lowering
     FreshRSS refresh cadence (≥15 min) avoids auto-removal after
     consecutive 429s.
     Sources with NO native RSS are listed as comments at the end → use rss-bridge.
     Import: FreshRSS ▸ Subscription management ▸ Import ▸ upload this file. -->
